edback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 24, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104clr1665703536847.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/clr1665703536847.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/clr1665703536847.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"clr1665703536847\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Every Uniface application looks for global assignments in a file called <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.asn</span> in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">USYSADM:</code> (<span class=\"ph filepath\">/adm</span>) subdirectory of the Uniface installation directory.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"clr1665703536847__section_w1774ab1b5b1_w1775ab1b5_w1776ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"clr1665703536847__table_d18683e1_d18684e1_d18685e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default location:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceInstallDir</var>/common/adm</span>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"clr1665703536847__section_w1777ab1b5b3_w1778ab1b5_w1779ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d265039e89\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"clr1665703536847__p_d177320e1_d177321e1_d177322e1\">Uniface uses the assignments from the <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.asn</span> file, along with any local assignments that it can locate, to create its internal assignments file. The global assignments should be designed to serve all applications as a fall-back for objects that are not assigned locally.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"clr1665703536847__p_d177323e1_d177324e1_d177325e1\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.asn</span> file is not automatically read by all Uniface applications. It must be included in the application assignment file using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">#file</span>. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104clr1665703536847_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"clr1665703536847__codeblock_zjl_3gz_gwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#file C:/Progam Files/Uniface/Uniface10/common/adm/usys.asn</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aoa1665702739697.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Assignment Files</a><p>A Uniface assignment file contains one or more assignment settings, which determine the environment of a Uniface application and control aspects of its behavior. Assignment settings can determine the location of application resources and servers, set environment variables, define application logicals, and set Uniface system settings to influence runtime behavior.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eao1665702739907.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuration Settings: Assignment</a><p>Assignment files contain assignments and settings that define the environment of a Uniface application. Assignments tell Uniface where to find the resources, connectors, servers and external components that the application needs, and how to connect to them. Assignment settings define other aspects of the application behavior.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526507\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "usys.asn Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 24, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Every Uniface application looks for global assignments in a file called usys.asn in the USYSADM: ( /adm ) subdirectory of the Uniface installation directory. Default location: UnifaceInstallDir /common/adm Description Uniface uses the assignments from the usys.asn file, along with any local assignments that it can locate, to create its internal assignments file. The global assignments should be designed to serve all applications as a fall-back for objects that are not assigned locally. The usys.asn file is not automatically read by all Uniface applications. It must be included in the application assignment file using #file . For example: Explain this code #file C:/Progam Files/Uniface/Uniface10/common/adm/usys.asn Copy Related Links Assignment Files A Uniface assignment file contains one or more assignment settings, which determine the environment of a Uniface application and control aspects of its behavior. Assignment settings can determine the location of application resources and servers, set environment variables, define application logicals, and set Uniface system settings to influence runtime behavior. Configuration Settings: Assignment Assignment files contain assignments and settings that define the environment of a Uniface application. Assignments tell Uniface where to find the resources, connectors, servers and external components that the application needs, and how to connect to them. Assignment settings define other aspects of the application behavior. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}